5:
So that's the sitch. Of course, we
don't know if the intel is 100% correct,
so I'd like to keep looking into it.
9:
If that's the case, then I definitely
want to be there. I should go.
14:
Don't worry, we'll accompany Echo!
You can leave her in our hands.
18:
Okay. That's a big help, Primula.
We're counting on you.
22:
Yeah, Echo's having such a good
time, it'd suck to cut her fun short.
27: It is decided then! Adieu, my friends!
34:
Wow! So this is what a limestone
cavern looks like!
37:
This is my first time seeing one too...
It's just so... beautiful.
41:
Water and various byproducts from
eroding bedrock flow into the cave,
producing the almost ice-like pillars
you see here.
47:
Wow! Are you some kind of cave
scientist too, Echo?! Incredible!
51:
Wh-what? No, I only know the most
basic information. I'm not that
well-read...
54:
It's just... someone taught me about
these caves a long time ago. I'm
only going off what I remember.
58:
Ooh. Was it an old sweetheart of
yours? Someone you fancied?
62: No. At least, not like that.
65:
I did look up to them, though. They
inspired me.
67:
She was doing research on how to
protect the environment... The place
from my memories that I
mentioned—she was the one who
told me about it.
72: Narcissa... I'd like you to have these.
74:
I took lots of them! They're photos of
us. I...
77: Trying to make memories, are you?
82:
Oh... I think I understand, Echo. You
were avoiding it.
86:
Yes... I really had no intention of ever
going back there again. Not after
the last time.
89:
She... was very strong. The type of
person who never looked back,
always forged ahead.
91:
Me, on the other hand... I always
stood still, looking back at my
memories, trying to replicate them.
94:
I know I shouldn't be that way. I know
that those memories aren't worth
anything... but...
98:
Oh, I'm so sorry. I didn't mean to
blab on and on about myself like
that. I'm sorry for boring you.
102:
But... It's clear that she meant a lot to
you. That's why you miss her so
much, right?
111:
Oh, um. Never mind! Forget I said
anything—I can't possibly know how
you must feel!
116:
Okay! I'm thinking we get Echo here
to take some awesome pictures of
us!
120:
Really? But my pictures aren't
anything special, they—
127:
Let's make ourselves some new
memories, people!
131:
If that's the case, then Echo's gotta
be in the frame too!
133:
I'll snap the pic myself. Mind if I
borrow that camera of yours?
141:
All right everyone, places please!
Line up!
158:
"Arrangement"? What are we, food
on a plate?
165:
Come on everyone, closer together!
Squeeeze tighter! Tighter, I said!
176:
Yes, Chef! How about this, are we
packed in tight enough?
181:
Yes, yes, just like that! Closer,
everyone! Get right in there!
192:
Phew! I think we've got ourselves a
keeper!
196:
Oh wow. That's a surprisingly good
photo.
205:
There's just something... wonderful
about it!
215:
Hehe. Okay, then we'll have to take
another one when we get to that
special spot of yours, Echo!
224:
Still wasting your time making
meaningless memories, I see.
234:
We're leaving, Echo. Spare
yourself—and the others—the
disappointment.
